text: Welcome to Lake Forest Addition, One of Grapevines Most Sought-After Lake Communities! This rare and unique property offers a true lake lifestyle with two separate lots, two parcels, and two addresses, including a deeded boat slip just steps away! Situated on a generous 0.54-acre combined lot, the property includes the main home at 2006 Forest Hills and a second lot directly behind at 3512 Lakeridge Dr. Parcel ID 01546945 Enjoy partial lake views of Grapevine Lake from the front of the home and imagine even more breathtaking vistas with the addition of a second story. Both lots are shaded with mature trees, creating a serene and private atmosphere.The main home offers 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms with a thoughtful split-bedroom layout. Two spacious living areas, ideal for entertaining, a game room, or a flex space. Beautiful hardwood floors in the main living and dining areas, hallways, and one bedroom. Semi-updated kitchen and baths a backyard retreat featuring a large concrete patio, pergola, and dual street access. Detached 2-car garage plus a 2-car carport with workshop space. This home includes your own deeded BOAT SLIP at the private community marina a luxury that rarely comes available in this neighborhood. Whether youre looking to enjoy as-is or explore future development potential, the endless possibilities and premium location make this a truly special offering. Dont miss your chance to live the lake life in one of Grapevines finest communities!

text: Own a Piece of Grapevine History - The Iconic Blevins Farmhouse: A rare opportunity to own one of Grapevine's most treasured historic homes - the Blevins Farmhouse. This beautifully restored Queen Anne Victorian, originally built in 1903, has been thoughtfully updated to offer the perfect blend of vintage charm and modern convenience. A true landmark, the home was named for its original owners and generously donated to the City of Grapevine in 2017. It was carefully relocated from Continental Boulevard to the Historic Township, where its legacy continues to be preserved for future generations. Thoughtfully renovated between 2017 and 2020, the Blevins Farmhouse features an open-concept design with warm modern farmhouse finishes. Inside, you'll find light-filled living and kitchen spaces adorned with plantation shutters-ideal for entertaining. The owner's suite is a private retreat, complete with a cozy fireplace, soaking tub, dual showers, double vanity, and a spacious walk-in closet. No detail was overlooked in ensuring both beauty and functionality. Major systems-including foam insulation, windows, HVAC, plumbing, electrical, and even the foundation-were all updated and replaced, offering peace of mind and long-term energy efficiency. Located just two blocks from Historic Main Street, the home offers walkable access to Grapevine's vibrant shops, restaurants, wine-tasting rooms, and beloved community festivals. Whether you're drawn to architectural significance, historical charm, or a truly unique home with modern amenities, the Blevins Farmhouse is a one-of-a-kind gem ready for its next chapter.

text: Welcome to Your Dream Home in Silver Lake! Nestled on a peaceful cul-de-sac in the highly sought-after Silver Lake neighborhood, this beautifully maintained David Weekley home offers the perfect blend of charm, comfort, and convenience. With 3 spacious bedrooms, 2 full baths, and a dedicated office, there's plenty of room for work, relaxation, and entertaining. Enjoy quiet mornings on the shaded front porch with a cooling ceiling fan, or host memorable gatherings on the extended backyard patio. Step inside to find rich hand-scraped hardwood floors, elegant crown molding, and a layout designed for both style and function. The expansive owners suite is a true retreat, featuring a luxurious garden tub, a separate walk-in shower, and a generous walk-in closet. The secondary bedrooms share a convenient Jack-and-Jill bathroom, ideal for families or guests. The chef-inspired kitchen is outfitted with stunning marble countertops, a newer stovetop and dishwasher, and recent upgrades including a new faucet and disposal. Peace of mind comes with major updates already completed: New roof (2023) New AC (2022) Freshly painted exterior (2025) Location is everythingand this home has it all. Just a short stroll to Grapevines vibrant Main Street, you'll be steps away from award-winning restaurants, boutique shopping, and year-round festivals. For outdoor lovers, Grapevine Lake and its scenic trails and bike paths are just minutes away. With easy access to DFW Airport, Grapevine Mills, and Southlake Town Squareall within a 10-minute driveyoure perfectly positioned to enjoy the best of the DFW area. Experience the charm of lake life, the excitement of Main Street, and the warmth of a welcoming communityall from the comfort of your new home.

Step inside to find recent renovations featuring a beautifully updated kitchen and a luxurious primary suite bathroom, both with stylish, modern finishes. The thoughtful layout includes separate in-law quarters complete with a dedicated kitchen, living area, and bathroom-ideal for multigenerational living or guests. Car enthusiasts and adventurers will love the oversized 4-car garage and dedicated RV storage. This home is perfect for those seeking space, tranquility, and functionality-with room to entertain, relax, and enjoy nature just outside your door. Solar panels will be paid off with sale of the home. The solar panels have reduced the sellers monthly electric bill by hundreds of dollars. Close to Downtown Grapevine, Lake Grapevine, Restaurants, and Parks.

Upstairs the family room and kitchen overlook the private tree covered backyard with a perfectly located balcony off the kitchen to enjoy a meal with a stunning view or to watch a game with prewiring for a tv. Enter the luxurious primary bathroom that was renovated in 2024 and includes an oversized steam shower, heated floors, a therapeutic tub, heated towel bar, dual vanities with LED mirrors and a thoughtfully placed nook with built-in lighting highlighting the stunning tile. An expansive balcony is located just beyond the exercise room off the primary bedroom. Another bedroom features a walk-in closet with a remodeled en suite bathroom and its own private balcony which is a great place for star gazing at night and views for miles on a clear day. With a highly sought after cul de sac location minutes from DFW airport, major highways, award wining GCISD elementary, middle and high school plus easy access to Parr Park playgrounds and miles of connected trails, get ready to call this your new home.

text: Every home has a story. This one just happens to have chapters that span more than a century. Welcome to the GE Hurst Historical Houseoriginally constructed in 1910 and reborn in 2018 through a meticulous renovation that preserved its soul while anchoring it in the now. Set on a lush .54-acre lot filled with mature native trees, this home feels like a page out of Grapevines past with a future-proof foundationliterallybuilt atop a modern steel pier-and-beam system. With over 4, 560 square feet under roof and 2, 780 square feet of conditioned living space, the layout is as thoughtful as it is functional. Downstairs, the primary suite offers privacy and comfort with a spa-like en suite bath, while a guest suite on the same floor provides hospitality with ease. A light-filled great room flows into the heart of the homean updated kitchen and dining area designed for gathering. Upstairs, two additional bedrooms each feature full baths, accompanied by a large second living area and an expansive office space that could double as a creative studio or library. The details tell the real storypreserved trimwork, wide-plank floors, antique-inspired fixturesall balanced by smart updates and energy-efficient systems. Outside, a 960 sq ft detached garage-workshop echoes the aesthetic of a classic Texas barn, offering functionality with curb appeal. And the porte-cochere near the mudroom and laundry isnt just a design featureits a daily convenience. This is more than a historical homeits a legacy, lovingly restored and ready for its next chapter.

text: REMODELED AND ADDITIONAL SQUARE FOOTAGE ADDED... This beautiful Grapevine ISD home has undergone a remodel and now includes additional square footage. It is a 4 bedroom, 3.5 bathroom home. It has a dedicated office that can be used as a 5th bedroom. The home has had only one owner. In 2005 the master bedroom and master bathroom were remodeled, and an ensuite bathroom was added to bedroom #2. The master bedroom has two walk in closets, and the ensuite master bathroom was remodeled in 2016. It features a large tiled walk in shower with two shower heads, and a dedicated vanity area. All the bedrooms are upstairs with ceiling fans, walk in closets, and hard wood flooring through out. Bedroom #3, #4 share a hall bathroom that was remodeled in 2015. Upon entering the home, you will be greeted by a large, beautiful metal and glass front door. The large formal dining area is off the front entry and kitchen area, making it a great space for entertaining or hosting large family gatherings. The open concept living and kitchen area was remodeled in 2020, featuring a pantry, dry bar, eat in kitchen bar, granite countertops, new tile backsplash, new fireplace tiles, and tile throughout the first floor. Kitchen also features gas cooktop and black oven, black microwave, and black dishwasher. All this leads through another metal glass door to a beautiful lush landscaped private backyard oasis, which boasts a newly resurfaced chlorine pool in 2024. Additionally, a large laundry room and half bath, conveniently located next to the office, leads to a side yard with artificial turf, perfect for our furry friends. Also on the side yard is a large garden bin that sits on a concrete slab. Furthermore, a new roof was installed Sept 2024. Bathroom to Bedroom #2 was remodeled again in 2023. Blinds or shutters throughout the house. With numerous upgrades this home is a must see!!!

text: One-of-a-kind custom home in the prestigious Grapevine Lake community, located within award-winning Carroll ISD. text: PRICE ADJUSTMENT on this Location, location! Offering not only this beautiful neighborhood but this updated 4 bedrooms, 2.5 bath home in a sought-after Colleyville Grapevine school. An entry into the home from the rear yard brings you into an enclosed storage area or mud room with access into the kitchen area of the home. The home includes 2 water heaters and 3 Zoned HVAC units.

This lot is the perfect place to build your dream home and create a lifetime of memories.
